This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Additionally, the paper uses Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) which are commonly used in NLP tasks. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with acoustic modelling and speech signals. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (BLSTM) which are popular machine learning techniques. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with a task that involves human-like intelligence, i.e., speech recognition. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses neural networks, which are a subset of machine learning techniques that are inspired by the structure and function of the human brain.
